original: Carlstedt, Edit Maria (Maja), ämneslärarinna, Tidaholm, f. 4/7/87 i As-ker, Örebro 1., av pred. A. L. Larsson o. Anna Pettersson. G. 19 m. rektor K. E. Carlstedt. Barn: se denne. — Stud:ex. i Örebro 06, fil. mag. i Upps. 09, provår 14. Res. t. Frankr. 07, Tyskl. 12. Vik. lär. v. Västerås lärov. f. fl. 08, lär. i Motala 09-13, i Tidaholm fr. 13, ämnes’lär. i tyska, eng. o. franska v. Tidaholms samrealsk. sed. 33.
translated: Carlstedt, Edit Maria (Maja), subject teacher, Tidaholm, born July 4th, 1887 in Asker, Örebro County, daughter of the minister A. L. Larsson and Anna Pettersson. Married in 1909 to the principal K. E. Carlstedt. Children: see him. Studied for matriculation in Örebro in 1906, received a Bachelor's degree in Uppsala in 1909, and was a trainee in 1914. Traveled to France in 1907 and Germany in 1912. Substitute teacher at Västerås high school in 1908, a teacher in Motala from 1909-1913, in Tidaholm since 1913, a subject teacher in German, English, and French at Tidaholm's secondary school since 1933.
